1. // RwLock Deadlock Audit (T041, 2026-03-09):
2. // - All RwLock/Mutex guards are dropped before any `.await` point.
3. //   `record_tool_latency` explicitly calls `drop(latencies)` before the
4. //   atomic increment; `latency_percentiles` explicitly calls `drop(latencies)`
5. //   before the sort.  All other guard acquisitions are either the sole await
6. //   in a method or are released via implicit drop before the next await.
7. // - Rust's `!Send` bound on `MutexGuard` / `RwLockGuard` would produce a
8. //   compile-time error if any guard were held across an await in a multi-
9. //   threaded context, providing a mechanical safety net on top of the audit.
10. // - Connection and tool-call counts use `AtomicUsize` / `AtomicU64` which
11. //   need no locking at all.
12. // - No lock is held across I/O operations.
13. // Verdict: no deadlock potential identified.
